            <div class="ramadan-dua">
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <h4>ramadan Dua for (Fasting)</h4>
                        <p>This is the dua for opening fast (or dua for keeping fast), which is what we called Sahur (Sahoor). The dua in Arabic is as follows:</p>
                        <b>وَبِصَوْمِ غَدٍ نَّوَيْتُ مِنْ شَهْرِ رَمَضَانَ</b>
                        <p><b>Transliteration :</b>Wa bisawmi ghadinn nawaiytu min shahri Ramadan. [Source: no source]</p>
                        <p><b>translate :</b>I intent to keep fast today for the month of Ramadaan</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <h4>Ramadan Dua for (Iftar Dua)</h4>
                        <p>This is the dua for opening fast (or dua for keeping fast), which is what we called Sahur (Sahoor). The dua in Arabic is as follows:</p>
                        <b>ذَهَبَ الظَّمَأُ وَابْتَلَّتِ الْعُرُوقُ وَثَبَتَ الأَجْرُ إِنْ شَاءَ اللَّهُ</b>
                        <p><b>Transliteration :</b>Dhahaba al-zama’ wa abtalat al-‘urooq wa thabata al-ajr in sha Allaah [Source: Abu Dawud 2357]</p>
                        <p><b>translate :</b>Thirst is gone, the veins are moistened and the reward is certain if Allaah wills.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <h4>First 10 Days of Mercy</h4>
                        <b>يَا حَيُّ يَا قَيُّومُ بِرَحْمَتِكَ أَسْتَغيثُ</b>
                        <p><b>translate :</b>Oh Everliving, The Everlasting, I seek Your help through Your mercy.</p>

                        <hr>

                        <h4>Second 10 Days of Forgiveness</h4>
                        <b>اَسْتَغْفِرُ اللہَ رَبِّی مِنْ کُلِّ زَنْبٍ وَّ اَتُوْبُ اِلَیْہِ</b>
                        <p><b>translate :</b>I seek forgiveness from Allah for all my sins and turn to Him.</p>

                        <hr>

                        <h4>Last 10 Days of Seek Refuge with Allah from Hellfire</h4>
                        <b>اللَّهُمَّ إِنَّكَ عَفُوٌّ كَرِيمٌ تُحِبُّ الْعَفْوَ فَاعْفُ عَنِّي</b>
                        <p><b>translate :</b>O Allah! You are The One Who pardons greatly, and loves to pardon, so pardon me.</p>
                        <p> * disclaimer this ramadan date and time are based on kolkata shahri jamiat ahle hadees</p>

                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>



        </div>
    </div>



